ll>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''Unio Transfer, Philadelphia, PA''\n|\n* 05/06/2019 <small></small>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''09:30 Club, Washington, DC''\n|\n* 05/07/2019 <small></small>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''The Fox Theatre, Boulder, CO''\n|\n* 05/18/2019 <small></small>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://wallowsmusic.com/ Official website]\n\n[[Category:Atlantic Records artists]]\n[[Category:Alternative rock groups from California]]\n[[Category:Indie rock musical groups from California]]\n[[Category:American musical trios]]\n[[Category:Musical groups from Los Angeles]]\n[[Category:Surf music groups]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American indie rock band}}\n{{about|the American band|the geographic landform|The Wallows}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = Wallows\n| image            = File:Wallows Approved Press Photo from Warner Music Atlantic.jpg\n| image_size       = \n| image_upright    = \n| caption          = \n| background       = group_or_band\n| alias            = \n| origin           = [[Los Angeles]], [[Southern California]], U.S.\n| genre            = {{flatlist|\n* [[Indie rock]]<ref name=\"all music genres\">{{cite web |title=Wallows - Biography |url=https://www.allmusic.com/artist/wallows-mn0003719550/biography |website=Allmusic |accessdate=April 11, 2019 |quote=By the time Los Angeles' is Wallows began releasing music under that name in 2017, they had established an '80s-influenced sound with hints of post-punk, synth pop, and power pop as well as more down-to-earth contemporary bedroom pop.}}</ref>\n* [[post-punk]]<ref name=\"all music genres\"/>\n* [[power pop]]<ref name=\"all music genres\"/>\n* [[bedroom pop]]<ref name=\"all music genres\"/>\n* [[alternative rock]]<ref>{{cite web |last1=Silver |first1=Michael |title=Wallows Announce Debut Album & World Tour: Watch 'Are You Bored Yet?' Video Starring Noah Centineo, More |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/8496151/wallows-debut-album-world-tour-are-you-bored-yet-video |website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |accessdate=April 10, 2019 |date=February 1, 2019}}</ref>\n* [[Surf punk (music genre)|surf punk]]<ref>{{cite web |last1=Wass |first1=Mike |title=Wallows On Taking Risks, Their Debut LP & \"Pictures Of Girls\" Theories: Interview |url=https://www.idolator.com/7679773/wallows-interview-debut-album |website=Idolator |accessdate=11 April 2019|date=2018-05-16 }}</ref>}}\n| years_active     = {{start date|2017}}\u2013present\n| label            = [[Atlantic Records|Atlantic]]\n| website          = [https://wallowsmusic.com/ Official website]\n| current_members  = *[[Braeden Lemasters]]\n*Cole Preston\n*[[Dylan Minnette]]\n}}\n'''Wallows''' is an American [[Rock music|rock]] band based in [[Los Angeles]] composed of [[Braeden Lemasters]], Cole Preston, and [[Dylan Minnette]]. The band began releasing songs independently in April 2017 starting with \"Pleaser\", which reached number two on the [[Spotify]] Global [[Viral 50]] chart. In 2018, they signed a record deal with [[Atlantic Records]] and released their major label debut extended play ''Spring''. Their debut studio album, ''[[Nothing Happens (album)|Nothing Happens]]'', was released in 2019 and included the single \"Are You Bored Yet?\".\n\n==History==\nThe band's three members\u2014Braeden Lemasters (guitar and vocals), Cole Preston (drums), and Dylan Minnette (guitar and vocals)\u2014first formed a musical group as children in a music program: GigMasterz in Keyboard Galleria Music Center ([[Southern California]]), they were called \"Join the Band\". Over the course of the next decade, the three performed together using different band names. They also played the 2011 [[Warped Tour]].<ref name=\"Chron\">{{cite news | last=Spuhler| first=Robert| title =Breakout band Wallows kicks off headlining tour in SF| newspaper =San Francisco Chronicle| date =January 17, 2018| url =https://www.sfchronicle.com/music/article/Breakout-band-Wallows-kicks-off-headlining-tour-12504935.php| accessdate =April 9, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"SubLeaves\">{{cite news | last=Hudelson| first=Molly| title =Wallows release new single 'Pulling Leaves Off Trees'| website=Substream Magazine| date =November 21, 2017| url =https://substreammagazine.com/2017/11/wallows-pulling-leaves-off-trees/| accessdate =April 9, 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn April 2017, the band released their first single under the Wallows moniker, \"Pleaser\".<ref name=\"TV\">{{cite news | last=Elizabeth| first=De| title =13 Reasons Why's Dylan Minnette Announces Band's First Single| work=Teen Vogue| date =April 13, 2017| url =https://www.teenvogue.com/story/13-reasons-why-dylan-minnette-band-first-single| accessdate =April 9, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"Nylon\">{{cite news | last=Gore| first=Sydney| title ='13 Reasons Why' You're Going To Love Wallows| website=Nylon| date =April 13, 2017| url =https://nylon.com/articles/dylan-minnette-wallows-pleaser| accessdate =April 9, 2018}}</ref> The song would eventually reach number two on the Spotify Global Viral 50 chart and number one on the [[KROQ-FM|KROQ]] Locals Only playlist.<ref name=\"SubLeaves\"/> In May 2017, Wallows released a second single, \"Sun Tan\",<ref name=\"Euph\">{{cite news | last=Ersoy| first=Laura| title =Wallows - Sun Tan| website=Euphoria| date =May 22, 2017| url =http://www.euphoriazine.com/blog/2017/05/new-music/tracks-wallows-sun-tan/| accessdate =April 9, 2018}}</ref> and began playing live shows in the Los Angeles area, selling out The Roxy and the [[Troubadour (West Hollywood, California)|Troubadour]].<ref name=\"Sugar\">{{cite news | last=Garcia| first=Kelsey| title =We Need to Talk About Dylan Minnette's Band \u2014 Because It's Really Good!| website =PopSugar| date =May 10, 2017| url =https://www.popsugar.com/entertainment/Dylan-Minnette-Band-Wallows-43523191| accessdate =April 9, 2018}}</ref> Their third single, \"Uncomfortable\", was released in September 2017.<ref name=\"SubComfort\">{{cite news | last=Hudelson| first=Molly| title =Prepare to get 'Uncomfortable' with Wallows' new single| website=Substream Magazine| date =September 14, 2017| url =https://substreammagazine.com/2017/09/wallows-uncomfortable/| accessdate =April 9, 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn November 2017, their song, \"Pulling Leaves Off Trees\", was premiered on [[Zane Lowe]]'s [[Beats 1]] radio show.<ref name=\"VarianceLeaves\">{{cite news | last=Howard| first=Lindsay| title =Hear Wallows' Breezy New Track 'Pulling Leaves Off Trees'| website=Variance| date =November 16, 2017| url =http://variancemagazine.com/sounds/8634-wallows-pulling-leaves-off-trees| accessdate =April 9, 2018}}</ref> That month, the band also announced their first headlining North American tour that would run from January to March 2018.<ref name=\"OTW\">{{cite news | last=Otero| first=Gabriela| title =NEW ARTIST DISCOVERY: Young Alt-Rock Trio Wallows Releases New Single & 2018 Tour Dates| website=Ones to Watch| date =November 29, 2017| url =http://www.onestowatch.com/blog/new-artist-discovery-young-alt-rock-trio-wallows| accessdate =April 9, 2018}}</ref> The tour started in [[San Francisco]] on January 24.<ref name=\"Chron\"/><ref name=\"Nexus\">{{cite news | last=Jackson| first=Hannah| title =Indie Act Wallows Ignites Velvet Jones| newspaper =Daily Nexus| date =February 3, 2018| url =http://dailynexus.com/2018-02-03/indie-act-wallows-ignites-velvet-jones/| accessdate =April 9, 2018}}</ref> In February 2018, the band announced that they had signed to [[Atlantic Records]] and were planning to release their major label debut EP, ''Spring'', in April 2018. They also released a new single, \"Pictures of Girls\", their first on Atlantic.<ref name=\"SubAtlantic\">{{cite news | last=Hudelson| first=Molly| title =Wallows sign to Atlantic Records; release 'Pictures Of Girls'| website=Substream Magazine| date =February 27, 2018| url =https://substreammagazine.com/2018/02/wallows-atlantic-records-pictures-of-girls/| accessdate =April 9, 2018}}</ref> The song was chosen as a \"Critical Cut\" by [[SiriusXM]] [[Alt Nation]].<ref name=\"Verge\">{{cite news | last=Mohaghegh| first=Neelu| title =Wallows Releases Nostalgic Single \"These Days\" Worth Not Missing| work=Verge Campus | date =March 23, 2018| url =https://vergecampus.com/2018/03/wallows-releases-nostalgic-days/| accessdate =April 9, 2018}}</ref>\n\nWallows ended their North American tour at [[South by Southwest]] in March 2018.<ref name=\"OTW\"/><ref name=\"VarianceDays\">{{cite news | last=Howard| first=Lindsay| title =Listen to Wallows' Summery New Track 'These Days'| website=Variance| date =March 26, 2018| url =http://variancemagazine.com/sounds/9037-wallows-these-days| accessdate =April 9, 2018}}</ref> Later in the month, they released a second track from ''Spring'' titled \"These Days\".<ref name=\"VarianceDays\"/> The EP was released on April 6, 2018 by Atlantic Records and was produced by [[John Congleton]].<ref name=\"MTVSpring\">{{cite news | last=Gore| first=Sydney| title =Wallows Lead Us To Believe That Spring Is Really Here| publisher =MTV| date =April 6, 2018| url =http://trl.mtv.com/news/3072656/wallows-spring-ep/| accessdate =April 9, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"Stereo\">{{cite news | last=Helman| first=Peter| title =Wallows \u2013 '1980s Horror Film'| website = Stereogum| date =April 5, 2018| url =https://www.stereogum.com/1989975/wallows-1980s-horror-film/premiere/| accessdate =April 9, 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn February 1, 2019, Wallows released the single \"Are You Bored Yet?\" featuring [[Clairo]]. This song is a part of their debut album, ''Nothing Happens'', released on March 22, 2019. A subsequent music video was also released on this day with a cameo of [[Noah Centineo]] and [[Kaitlyn Dever]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wlgmyE5Juzw|title=YouTube|website=www.youtube.com|access-date=2019-02-03}}</ref> \n\nWallows embarked on another leg of their ''Nothing Happens Tour'' in February 2020, a continuation of their 2019 ''Nothing Happens Tour'', for 15 additional stops.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/live/8531740/wallows-2020-tour-animated-felt-video-treacherous-doctor|title=Wallows Announce 2020 Tour, Release Animated Felt Video for \u00e2\u20ac\u02dcTreacherous Doctor\u00e2\u20ac\u2122|date=2019-09-30|website=Billboard|access-date=2020-03-11}}</ref> The band partnered with local, non-profit charities in each of the cities in this leg of the tour such as [https://www.projectlazarus.net Project Lazarus] and the [https://www.lgbtcenterofraleigh.com LGBT Center of Raleigh].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vCO7ZLuOwaQ|title=Wallows share stories of tour life, a bus FIRE and alternative band names!|author=97X Videos|date=February 21, 2020|website=Youtube|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> Before each show, the band posted a list of donatable items for their attendees to bring (with the incentive of donating being a free Wallows pin) on their social media accounts, and were able to garner a plethora of items to donate after each show.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/wallowsmusic/status/1228055066344673280|title=tour starts today and we're very happy to be partnering with local nonprofits in every city we play. it would mean the world to us if you brought any of the items listed for the charity listed in the city you're coming to see us in. if you do, you'll get a free pin :)pic.twitter.com/tiOTTXx7Sq|last=Wallows|date=2020-02-13|website=@wallowsmusic|language=en|access-date=2020-03-11}}</ref> In an interview with [[WSUN (FM)|97X]], a Tampa radio station, [[Dylan Minnette|Minnette]] remarked that the nonprofit organization they partnered with in Fort Lauderdale, Florida, [https://handyinc.org Handy Inc.], shared that Wallows fans had brought an equivalent of five months worth of supplies to the band\u2019s show.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n==Members==\n* [[Dylan Minnette]] \u2013 vocals, rhythm guitar, keyboards {{small|(2017\u2013present)}}\n* [[Braeden Lemasters]] \u2013 vocals, lead guitar, bass guitar {{small|(2017\u2013present)}}\n* Cole Preston \u2013 drums, backing vocals {{small|(2017\u2013present)}}\n\n==Discography==\n===Albums===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+List of LPs with selected album details\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Details\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"1\"| Peak chart positions\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Billboard 200|US]]<br/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/wallows/chart-history/billboard-200|title=Wallows Chart History: Billboard 200|work=Billboard|accessdate=April 2, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Nothing Happens (album)|Nothing Happens]]''\n|\n* Release date: March 22, 2019\n* Label: [[Atlantic Records|Atlantic]]\n* Formats: [[Music download|Digital download]], [[Compact disc|CD]], [[Cassette tape|Cassette]], [[LP record|LP]]\n| 75\n|}\n\n===EPs===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+List of EPs with selected album details\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:10em\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:20em\"| Details\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''Spring''\n|\n* Released: April 6, 2018 <small>(US)</small>\n* Label: Atlantic\n* Formats: Digital download, LP, CD, Vinyl record\n|}\n\n===Singles===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of singles showing year released and album name\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:16em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Year\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"2\"| Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Album\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Alternative Songs|US<br/>Alt.]]<br/><ref name=\"US-Alternative-singles\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/wallows/chart-history/alternative-songs|title=Wallows Chart History: Alternative Songs|work=Billboard|accessdate=February 8, 2019}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Rock Songs|US<br/>Rock]]<br/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/wallows/chart-history/rock-songs|title=Wallows Chart History: Hot Rock Songs|work=Billboard|accessdate=February 19, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|\"Pleaser\"\n| rowspan=\"4\"|2017\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| rowspan=\"4\" {{n/a|Non-album singles}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|\"Sun Tan\"\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|\"Uncomfortable\"\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|\"Pulling Leaves Off Trees\"\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|\"Pictures of Girls\"\n| rowspan=\"5\" |2018\n| 39\n| \u2014\n| rowspan=\"2\"|''Spring''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|\"These Days\"\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|\"Underneath the Streetlights in the Winter Outside Your House\"\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| rowspan=\"3\" {{n/a|Non-album singles}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|\"1980s Horror Film II\" \n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|\"Drunk on Halloween\"\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|\"Are You Bored Yet?\"<br/>{{small|(featuring [[Clairo]])}}\n| rowspan=\"4\"| 2019\n| \u2014\n| 33\n| rowspan=\"3\"| ''Nothing Happens''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|\"Scrawny\"\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|\"Sidelines\"\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|\"Trust Fall\" / \"Just Like a Movie\"\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| {{n/a|Non-album single}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|\"OK\"\n| rowspan=\"2\"|2020\n| \u2014\n| 28\n| {{TBA}}\n|-\n|}\n\n===Tour===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+ Nothing Happens Tour\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:10em\"| Local\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:20em\"| Date\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''Coachella, Indio, CA''\n|\n* 04/13/2019 <small></small>\n* 04/20/2019 <small></small>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''Wonder Ballroom, Portland, OR''\n|\n* 04/22/2019 <small></small>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''Venue Nightclub, Vancouver, Canada''\n|\n* 04/23/2019 <small></small>\