ion|UMNO]])\n|align=\"right\" |11,942\n|40.3%<sup>2</sup>\n|{{Party shading/Sabah Heritage Party}} |\n|Karim Bujang ([[Sabah Heritage Party|WARISAN]])\n|align=\"right\" |11,786\n|39.8%<sup>2</sup>\n|-\n| colspan=\"9\" |{{small|Notes:<br />Table excludes votes for candidates who finished in third place or lower.<br /><sup>2</sup> Different % used for 2018 election.}}\n|}\n\n==Honours==\n* {{Flag|Pahang}} :\n** [[File:MY-PAH Order of the Crown of Pahang - Knight Companion - DIMP.svg|50px]] Knight Companion of the [[Orders, decorations, and medals of Pahang|Order of the Crown of Pahang]] (DIMP) - '''Dato'''' (2004)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theborneopost.com/2011/10/01/highest-state-award-for-eight/|date=26 October 2004|accessdate=14 September 2018|publisher=[[The Star (Malaysia)|The Star]]|title=Sultan of Pahang's 74th birthday honours list|work=}}</ref>\n** [[File:MY-PAH Order of Sultan Ahmad Shah of Pahang - Grand Knight - SSAP.svg|50px]] Grand Knight of the [[Orders, decorations, and medals of Pahang|Order of Sultan Ahmad Shah of Pahang]] (SSAP) - '''Dato' Sri''' (2009)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thestar.com.my/news/nation/2009/10/24/1114-to-receive-pahang-honours/|date=24 October 2009|accessdate=14 September 2018|publisher=[[The Star (Malaysia)|The Star]]|title=1,114 to receive Pahang honours|work=}}</ref>\n* {{Flag|Sabah}} :\n** [[File:MY-SAB Order of Kinabalu - PGDK.svg|50px]] Commander of the [[Order of Kinabalu]] (PGDK) - '''Datuk''' (1998)\n** [[File:MY-SAB Order of Kinabalu - SPDK.svg|50px]] Grand Commander of the [[Order of Kinabalu]] (SPDK) - '''Datuk Seri Panglima''' (2011)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theborneopost.com/2011/10/01/highest-state-award-for-eight/|date=1 October 2011|accessdate=14 September 2018|publisher=[[Borneo Post]]|title=Highest state award for eight|work=Sandra Sokial}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[List of foreign ministers in 2017]]\n\n== References ==\n<references />\n\n{{First Najib cabinet}}\n{{Second Najib cabinet}}\n{{P